OL,3,CWest Country Labour MPs divided over
OL,4,Cgovernment cuts to benefits
OL,6,FMultiple West Country Labour MPs have
OL,7,Fcome out against government plans to
OL,8,Fcut benefits, admitting that the
OL,9,Fmeasures would push more people in
OL,10,Ftheir constituencies into poverty.
OL,12,FDr Simon Opher, Stroud's MP has said
OL,13,Fhe will vote against the changes when
OL,14,Fthey come before Parliament, telling
OL,15,Fvoters he "did not come into politics
OL,16,Fto make life harder for those already
OL,17,Fstruggling."
OL,19,FHe added: "We must not balance the
OL,20,Fbooks on the backs of the poorest in
OL,21,Fsociety."
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/9
