OL,3,CWest Country Labour MPs divided over
OL,4,Cgovernment cuts to benefits
OL,6,FChancellor Rachel Reeves confirmed
OL,7,Fhuge cuts to benefits in her Spring
OL,8,FStatement on 26 March, and went even
OL,9,Ffurther than initial reports by
OL,10,Ffreezing the health element of
OL,11,FUniversal Credit to make even larger
OL,12,Fsavings.
OL,14,FThe government's own analysis
OL,15,Festimates that in 2029-30, 3.2 million
OL,16,Ffamilies will lose an average of
OL,17,F#1,720 a year as a result of the cuts,
OL,18,Fwith 250,000 people pushed into
OL,19,Frelative poverty.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/9
