OL,3,CWest Country Labour MPs divided over
OL,4,Cgovernment cuts to benefits
OL,6,F"I won't ignore the findings of the
OL,7,Findependent impact assessment
OL,8,Fpublished yesterday, which states that
OL,9,Fthese changes will push an extra
OL,10,F250,000 people (including 50,000
OL,11,Fchildren) into relative poverty after
OL,12,Fhousing costs."
OL,14,FDr Opher, who took Stroud from the
OL,15,FTories last year, said: "I also know
OL,16,Fthe negative effects of austerity;
OL,17,Fshortened healthy life expectancy,
OL,18,Fincreased mental health issues, and
OL,19,Flimited social mobility.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/9
