OL,3,CWest Country Labour MPs divided over
OL,4,Cgovernment cuts to benefits
OL,6,F"The government's own impact
OL,7,Fassessment makes it clear: these
OL,8,Fwelfare reforms will push 250,000
OL,9,Fpeople, including 50,000 children,
OL,10,Finto poverty.
OL,12,F"I did not come into politics to make
OL,13,Flife harder for those already
OL,14,Fstruggling. I will be voting against
OL,15,Fthese proposals when they come before
OL,16,FParliament."
OL,18,FAll MPs seem to agree on the need for
OL,19,Fwelfare reform, with the cost to the
OL,20,Fgovernment evidently skyrocketing.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G8/9
